    public abstract class CustomResultEditor
extends CustomEditor
    Abstract class that any custom CheckResult editors must implement. Note that this class is a subclass of CustomEditor, which has a number of important methods for you to implement as well.
    See Also:

    • Method Detail

      • setResultInfo

        public abstract void setResultInfo(java.util.List allNodes,
                 TestNodeInfo ni,
                 com.itko.lisa.editor.AssertControllerBase ri)
        This method is called on you whenever your CheckResult sublcass needs to be set for this object. You should be ready for this to be called on the same instance of your object; if this happens, forget about the other instance of CheckResult you were editing, and do this one.
        Parameters:
        allNodes - - this is a direct reference to all the nodes in the TestCase as a Vector of TestNodeInfo objects
        ni - - this is the specific TestNodeInfo that your CheckResult is for
        ri - - this is your AssertControllerBase object, the attributes of your particular CheckResult

      • migrate

        public abstract void migrate(Assertion tr)
        When a native Test Case XML document is loaded, a mechanism is needed to migrate the actual CheckResult object into Editor objects that will read their state and allow them to be edited and saved. This method gets called on you when a CheckResult of your type has been found in the Test Case. You should query your CheckResult for its unique attributes and store them into the AssertControllerBase.attribs Hashtable. NOTE: Don't store your attributes into this class!!!!!!! This editor class will have already been given the right AssertControllerBase object via a call to setResultInfo(). Store the subclass-specific state there.
        Parameters:
        tr - the CheckResult to read state from
